  "commentary": "With SPX at 6765.35 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6750 (-46B) and max positive gamma at 6800 (+30B), dealers are in active buy mode as they're short gamma and need to chase this move higher. The breakout regime with massive negative GEX concentration from 6750-6770 creates a volatile amplification zone where dealer buying pressure should accelerate any move toward the 6800 resistance wall where they'll flip to selling. Watch for continuation through 6770 which breaks the heaviest negative gamma cluster, likely triggering more mechanical buying toward 6800, while any pullback toward 6750 gets bought aggressively.\n\nBottom line: expect strong upward momentum with dealers buying the rip toward 6800.",
